SIMPLE: wardship
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wardship
<hw>Ward"ship</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
office of a ward or keeper; care and protection of a ward; guardianship;
right of guardianship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Wardship</qex> is incident to tenure in socage.</q>
<rj><qau>Blackstone.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of begin under a guardian;
pupilage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It was the wisest act . . . in my <qex>wardship</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>B. Jonson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wardsman</ent>⟦br⟧
